			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: NToV<a name="10893"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 2 03 7:15 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />

<br />
Being the only bard on a raid sucks.
<br />

<br />
NToV is a lot of fun, but it usually takes a long time to
<br />
get things done.
<br />

<br />
Usually the guild will want to coth to Aaryonar, and for him
<br />
I recommend elemental chorus, zek, rizlona's, and HoS/OoS
<br />
when you can.
<br />

<br />
After him the guild will move up to just passed where Aary
<br />
was, they call it &quot;the pit&quot; but you may know it as another
<br />
name.  There should be a few mobs pulled from there, and you
<br />
want both types of AE songs up, since some of the mobs
<br />
cast fire/cold/magic, while others poison/disease/magic.  I
<br />
believe it's easy to spot them by the color the mob is, but I
<br />
haven't been there in a long time.  I think blue=cold, red=fire,
<br />
green=poison, brown=disease.
<br />

<br />
The next 2-3 dragons will be pulled to the pit, or most likely
<br />
to one of the corners on the side of it, and they all have some
<br />
sort of AE, and since you're going to be the only bard, which
<br />
sucks, you're gonna have to take care of that primarily.
<br />
If you have fading memories, once you move out of pit to the
<br />
next dragons, you should try to follow him closely when he/she
<br />
charges, and play AE resists right after he/she engages.  Let's
<br />
just say that your guild needs to invest in recruiting 2-3 bards
<br />
minimum, and then we can talk about much more fun roles
<br />
bards can play on NToV raids.
<br />

<br />
good luck,
<br />

<br />
'Stuce</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
