			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: NToV<a name="10913"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 2 03 6:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Join the club Evaal... I've been there a few times and always was the only bard on the raid.  Like has been said here, it is boring, but essential, to play resists and resists only, if you can't keep up them continually in battle.  If you can, then you can play other songs to help your group, but if your resist songs go down, so does the raid.  I have spent time litterally running back and forth between the meleers up at the mob and then back to the exposed casters so both got pulses of my resist songs.  It was insane and boring, but when I stopped, we wiped. In downtime I played manasong, but never let resists drop when fighting casters, which is most of the time.  
<br />

<br />
It's a fun adrenaline burst, but the loot is iffy IMHO.  Folks like it as a right of passage for an up and coming guild.  I completely agree that 2 or 3 bards are a must for that place, being the only one sucks, but you make friends fast.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
