				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: NToV<a name="10953"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 6 03 8:32 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I would always just stand about halfway between the melee and the casters, and sing two and only two songs, AoE resists, and AoE mana.  I would twist those two, and twist my best drum and lute, as close to 50hp/tick regen+mana REALLY lessens the load on the clerics.  
<br />

<br />
I parsed one round in HoT and found the I did more healing than EVERYONE else combined, as the regen made up for the 20, 50, and 70 damage hits that most people were taking every now and again.  Getting AoE'd for 50 outta 300 or 500 possible isnt bad, but will make you still need a heal if you dont regen back to full in the time before the next one hits.
<br />

<br />
Also, have a hotkey set up as follows:
<br />

<br />
/rs We have an ADD!!  Its beating on the BARD!!
<br />
/disc deftdance
<br />
/rs Please offtank %T within the next 15 seconds or I will die
<br />

<br />

<br />
or something like that.  Every 3 seconds, you are gonna be doing something that will gain you MASSIVE aggro with any mob that is not actively engaged, so basically any and all adds will head straight to you.  If you cant tank 500 hitters, I suggest a key like that to keep you from dying, especially being the only bard there.
<br />

<br />
As for not playing mana, thats silliness.  Chorus of Marr will eliminate downtime completely, leaving the casters with near to full mana after each fight, which is a good thing.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
