				<td colspan="2"><span>I being pretty much the only bard that plays on a consistant basis althought we just got some new recruits and am in an lvl 65 elemental flagged raid guild find that my guild has many uses for me and i have lots, actually almost 25 different set-up for different mob and in different groups, i've pretty much grouped my entire life. Best thing to do is right off see what type of group your in and ask what songs peeps would like you to play and even get with the raid leader.
<br />

<br />
The best suggestion i can make is dont over do it. If they want you playing mana and resists  play mana and resists dont get fancy if a resist drops and the aoe hits and causes lots of problems trust me your the only one to get blamed.
<br />

<br />
Another suggestion is to stay on the sidelines if thats what you have to do playing for the casters, it gets boring but it's your job. I used to get right up there and fight with the rest of that tanks and i believe i died first almost everytime. Then i found that you do more for your raid singing.
<br />

<br />
It was stated up above to know your class...a bard played right is needed and used in almost every situation. </span></td>
